Click on the slide show to see this week’s featured properties in New York City:
• In Sutton Place, a two-bedroom, three-bath apartment with a gracious living room and fireplace in a 60-unit prewar mid-rise.
• In Carnegie Hill, a one-bedroom, one-bath co-op with a recently renovated kitchen and bathroom and lots of storage space in a postwar mid-rise.
• In Bay Ridge, Brooklyn, a three-bedroom, two-bath, recently renovated, light-filled condo with a loft-like living/dining/kitchen space, a foyer, a washer and dryer and a balcony in a 1957 104-unit doorman building. Indoor parking space sold separately for $90,000.
